    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-wine-700 mb-2">What's the difference between pairing wine with ribeye versus filet mignon?</h3>
    <p class="text-gray-700">Ribeye's higher fat content and marbling calls for full-bodied wines with bold tannins like Cabernet Sauvignon or Barolo to cut through the richness. Filet mignon's leaner, more delicate texture pairs beautifully with medium-bodied wines like Pinot Noir or Côtes du Rhône that won't overpower its subtle beef flavor. The key is matching the wine's intensity to the steak's fat content and flavor profile.</p>
