    <p class="text-gray-700">Red wines should be served slightly below room temperature at 60-65°F, not the typical 70-75°F room temperature. This cooler serving temperature enhances the wine's structure and prevents the alcohol from overwhelming the steak's flavors. Let the bottle sit in a cool place for 30 minutes before serving, or briefly chill it in the refrigerator for 15 minutes.</p>
